0c4c10b9-789a-417c-a21b-24c80c4f3ae6	2026-04-09 18:03:49.863042+00	2026-04-09 18:44:00.714762+00	\N	\N	0	0	Meeting: F6 Testing Set up\nAttendees: Karen Byrne, Tracy Highton, Bryan Hieber, John Shurts, Becky Martin, Lonnie Sanders, Michael Griffith, Funke Tijani, Jinny Brahmbhatt, Dinesh Gutta\n\nNotes:\n  Goal of meeting is to request F6 transactions generation for the purpose of F6 transactions flowing into HPNS audit logs for the CSDE / DRLS QA team to validate F6 updates.\n  Bryan Hieber’s team has been asked to assist with generating very limited transactions to test processes and F6 coding updates.\n  If additional transactions are needed, then leadership will be asked to identify other testing resources.\n  The Plan is to have this set up meeting then 1 week later have a session to review transaction results. Neither is a working session.\n  \n  The latest version(s) of WINTEST are located here: https://mckesson.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RHPD/pages/86550099076/WinTestTool\n  \n  You’ll want to configure connectivity (under tools -> settings) for this testing to:\n  Server (IP): 10.49.139.3\n  Port Number 9010\n  Port Type – 2 Tandem (Standard Pharmacy Header)\n  \n  \n  [cid:image001.png@01DCC765.64ECFF30]\n  \n  For these scenarios – Use Transaction Tester BIN\n  \n  Create an F6  B1 (billing) , B2 (reversal), B3 (Rebill)  and:\n  \n    *   Add all segments and fields, and populate them according to how WINTEST indicates the field should be populated (length/format)\n    *   For financial fields, Max out length (F6 increased field lengths)\n  Create one accepted and one rejected response or each using Transaction Tester\n  \n    *   Add all response segments and fields, and populate them according to how Transaction Tester indicates the field should be populated (length/format)\n    *   For financial fields, Max out length (F6 increased field lengths)\n  \n  Tracy created a couple of sample requests/responses with all fields and valid NDPCP values as a starting point.\n  \n  ________________________________\n  \n  Meeting Notes:\n  \n  - To get in the audit logs it WinTestTool has to point at the HPNS\n  - If Funke can get set up with WinTestTool and Transaction Tester they can do this is in the future\n  - Tracy built a sample F6 B1 with all fields\n    - We can create B2 from B1 in WinTestTool\n    - We believe a B3 is just a B1 with changed transaction type\n  - We need to save a date time when we send to make it easier for QA to find\n    - Give QA Rx#, DOS, NPI and a general date and time when we sent\n    - Jay Jackson can give us the Transaction Tester F6 guide\n	F6 Testing Set up	Goal of meeting is to request F6 transactions generation for the purpose of F6 transactions flowing into HPNS audit logs for the CSDE / DRLS QA team to validate F6 updates.\nBryan Hieber’s team has been asked to assist with generating very limited transactions to test processes and F6 coding updates.\nIf additional transactions are needed, then leadership will be asked to identify other testing resources.\nThe Plan is to have this set up meeting then 1 week later have a session to review transaction results. Neither is a working session.\n\nThe latest version(s) of WINTEST are located here: https://mckesson.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RHPD/pages/86550099076/WinTestTool\n\nYou’ll want to configure connectivity (under tools -> settings) for this testing to:\nServer (IP): 10.49.139.3\nPort Number 9010\nPort Type – 2 Tandem (Standard Pharmacy Header)\n\n\n[cid:image001.png@01DCC765.64ECFF30]\n\nFor these scenarios – Use Transaction Tester BIN\n\nCreate an F6  B1 (billing) , B2 (reversal), B3 (Rebill)  and:\n\n  *   Add all segments and fields, and populate them according to how WINTEST indicates the field should be populated (length/format)\n  *   For financial fields, Max out length (F6 increased field lengths)\nCreate one accepted and one rejected response or each using Transaction Tester\n\n  *   Add all response segments and fields, and populate them according to how Transaction Tester indicates the field should be populated (length/format)\n  *   For financial fields, Max out length (F6 increased field lengths)\n\nTracy created a couple of sample requests/responses with all fields and valid NDPCP values as a starting point.\n\n________________________________\n\nMeeting Notes:\n\n- To get in the audit logs it WinTestTool has to point at the HPNS\n- If Funke can get set up with WinTestTool and Transaction Tester they can do this is in the future\n- Tracy built a sample F6 B1 with all fields\n  - We can create B2 from B1 in WinTestTool\n  - We believe a B3 is just a B1 with changed transaction type\n- We need to save a date time when we send to make it easier for QA to find\n  - Give QA Rx#, DOS, NPI and a general date and time when we sent\n  - Jay Jackson can give us the Transaction Tester F6 guide
